{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-configure-magento-2-payment-failed-email/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Configure Magento 2 Payment Failed Email?","content":"\n<p>When managing an online store, it&#8217;s crucial to ensure a seamless checkout process for your customers. However, there may be instances where a customer experiences difficulties during payout. As a store owner, it&#8217;s essential to be aware of such issues and take necessary actions to resolve them. Fortunately, Magento offers several built-in features, including the payment failed email notification system, to help you in this regard. In this article, we will provide a detailed guide on <strong><em>how to configure Magento 2 payment failed email</em></strong> and explain why it&#8217;s crucial for the success of your online store.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Configure Magento 2 Payment Failed Email: A Comprehensive Guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Customize Failed Payment Email Template</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before setting up the payment failed to email in Magento 2, it&#8217;s necessary to make sure that your <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/simple-mail-transfer-protocol-smtp/\">SMTP</a> Email is properly set up for the task. Here&#8217;s <a href=\"/how-to-set-up-smtp-email-for-magento-2/\">how to set up SMTP Email for Magento 2</a>:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Enable the SMTP extension.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Go to Marketing &gt; Email Templates and create a new template to customize the payout failed email with your brand&#8217;s touch. You can personalize the template by adjusting the variables and adding your own design elements to the letter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With a properly set up SMTP Email for Magento 2, you can ensure that payout failed notifications are delivered efficiently and effectively to your customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Configure Magento 2 Payment Failed Email</h2>\n\n\n\n<