A16%3A22 492w,/_gatsby/image/d3c6d918f4d4216eb57a8c87692ee3e4/f06c8a3fd24a012600c0159b9884e07c/How-to-Configure-Magento-2-Payment-Failed-Email-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Configure-Magento-2-Payment-Failed-Email-01.png&a=w%3D983%26h%3D365%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-17T11%3A16%3A22 983w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 983px) 983px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":983,\"height\":365},\"alt\":\"How to Configure Magento 2 Payment Failed Email 01\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1522 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"1\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>1.Navigate to Stores &gt; Configuration &gt; Sales &gt; Checkout &gt; Payment Failed Emails.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Specify the Payment Failed Email Sender who will appear as the sender of the notification. You can choose from various options available in the dropdown menu, such as General Contact or Sales Representative.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Determine the Payment Failed Email Receiver who will receive the notification about the failed payment. This can be the store owner, customer service representative, or any other relevant person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: To set up emails for senders and receivers, make sure to configure Magento store email addresses.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Choose the Payment Failed Template that will be used for the notification. You can select from the available options or create a custom template.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Set the email address or addresses to Send the Payment Failed Email Copy To. If there are multiple recipients, separate them with a comma.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Determine the Payment Failed Copy Method for the email copy. You can choose from the options of None, Separate Email, or Add to Parent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s always essential to prioritize customer satisfaction and take extra steps to maintain a high level of customer experience. By knowing <strong><em>how to configure Magento 2 payment failed email</em></strong>, you can set up a payout failed email notification system and promptly address any issues that may arise during the transaction process. This useful feature ensures a seamless and hassle-free checkout experience for your customers, ultimately contributing to the success of your online store.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, knowing <strong><em>how to configure Magento 2 payment failed email</em></strong> is a crucial step towards ensuring a seamless and satisfactory experience for your customers. By following the steps provided in this article on <strong><em>how to set up Magento 2 payment failed email</em></strong>, you can easily establish a payout failed email notification system and take necessary actions to promptly address any issues that may arise. Always keep in mind that customer experience plays a vital role in the success of your online store, so it&#8217;s essential to implement useful features like this to maintain a high level of customer satisfaction.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-configure-magento-2-payment-failed-email/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+Configure+Magento+2+Payment+Failed+Email%3F+https%3A%2F%2Fwebg